name: Eric Sprague
tweet: 11/ The 2019 10-K shows that the stock did well from Dec 2014 to Dec 2019. In Dec '20 it was announced that $LMT is buying Aerojet $AJRD.  https://t.co/uGtF4m0fX9

name: Eric Sprague
tweet: 10/ The 2001 annual report noted that $LMT won the F-35 Lightning II Joint Strike Fighter program over Boeing and that it was arguably the most important competition in $LMT's history. In 2015 $LMT bought Sikorsky Aircraft Corporation (Sikorsky) for $9.0 billion

name: Eric Sprague
tweet: 9/ Prophets of War by William Hartung says $LMT's $350 Mn F-22 Raptor was the most expensive combat aircraft ever built. For some perspective,  https://t.co/QVruywe4gi says the 737 MAX is about $63 Mn.

name: Eric Sprague
tweet: 8/ The $LMT Rockwell team lost out to the $NOC $BA team for the high-priced B-2. Lockheed and Martin Marietta merged in 1995. The 1997 annual report says the F-22 Raptor rolled out in April of that year and had its 1st flight in September of that year.

name: Eric Sprague
tweet: 7/ $LMT competed for the B-2 contract; Ben said the govt. kept suppliers healthy, the largest was McDonnell Douglas (part of 987-bagger Boeing $BA) then 1,188-bagger General Dynamics $GD. $LMT was 3rd then 907-bagger Northrop $NOC & Rockwell (now part of 616-bagger Raytheon $RTX)

name: Eric Sprague
tweet: 2/ Developed by Skunk Works, the F-35 Lightning II generated 27% of 2019 sales. Ben Rich started at Skunk Works under Clarence "Kelly" Johnson in 1954 and he was promoted to the top spot in 1975 where he served until 1991. His Skunk Works book shows the innovation at $LMT.

name: Eric Sprague
tweet: 1/ Investing $10 thousand in Lockheed Martin $LMT in Dec 1971 worked out well as it eventually turned into over $13 Mn by '14 per the 100 Baggers book. In 1996 $LMT had sales of $26.9 Bn from 190k employees and by 2019 they had sales of $59.8 Bn from just 110k employees.
